    java.lang.Comparable<com.android.volley.Request<T>>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    GsonMultipartRequest

    public abstract class MultipartRequest<T>
extends FireRequest<T>
    So basically we need all the parts of this multipart request during construction of the request. We need a header for each part, which consists of Content-Disposition: form-data; name="my-control-name". We also need the data (of course), which can be either a string or a file. Created by stevetan on 18/11/14.
